The paper proposes a novel trilinear interaction model for Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of knowledge distillation, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on benchmarking datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
